l:dependency.name: LevelOps Plugin
l:dependency.l:description: Upload scan artifacts to LevelOps API

l:dependency.name: Jackson-dataformat-XML
l:dependency.l:description: Data format extension for Jackson (http://jackson.codehaus.org) to offer alternative support for serializing POJOs as XML and deserializing XML as pojos. Support implemented on top of Stax API (javax.xml.stream), by implementing core Jackson Streaming API types like JsonGenerator, JsonParser and JsonFactory. Some data-binding types overridden as well (ObjectMapper sub-classed as XmlMapper).

l:dependency.name: Commons BeanUtils
l:dependency.l:description: BeanUtils provides an easy-to-use but flexible wrapper around reflection and introspection.

l:dependency.name: Digester
l:dependency.l:description: The Digester package lets you configure an XML->Java object mapping module which triggers certain actions called rules whenever a particular pattern of nested XML elements is recognized.

l:dependency.name: Jackson-core
l:dependency.l:description: Core Jackson processing abstractions (aka Streaming API), implementation for JSON

l:dependency.name: Commons Validator
l:dependency.l:description: Commons Validator provides the building blocks for both client side validation and server side data validation. It may be used standalone or with a framework like Struts.

l:dependency.name: Woodstox
l:dependency.l:description: Woodstox is a high-performance XML processor that implements Stax (JSR-173), SAX2 and Stax2 APIs

l:dependency.name: jackson-databind
l:dependency.l:description: General data-binding functionality for Jackson: works on core streaming API

l:dependency.name: Jackson-annotations
l:dependency.l:description: Core annotations used for value types, used by Jackson data binding package.

l:dependency.name: Stax2 API
l:dependency.l:description: tax2 API is an extension to basic Stax 1.0 API that adds significant new functionality, such as full-featured bi-direction validation interface and high-performance Typed Access API.

l:dependency.name: Jackson module: JAXB Annotations
l:dependency.l:description: Support for using JAXB annotations as an alternative to "native" Jackson annotations, for configuring data-binding.
